[{"role": "system", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "You are an expert visceral surgeon analyzing surgical scene graphs.\n\nSCENE GRAPH STRUCTURE:\nYou are provided with a spatiotemporal scene graph representing a cholecystectomy procedure:\n- <objects>: Each object (node) is a distinct entity in the surgical scene (instruments or anatomy), represented by its visual appearance\n- <spatial-graphs>: A sequence of graphs over time, where each graph at timestep t contains:\n  - <node id=\"N\">: Spatial properties of object N at time t\n    - <center>: 3D position of the object's bounding box center\n    - <centroid>: 3D center of mass of the object\n    - <extent>: 3D size/dimensions of the object\n  - <edge from=\"N\" to=\"M\" dist=\"D\"/>: Spatial proximity between objects N and M (smaller distance = closer/interacting)\n\nGRAPH-BASED REASONING FOR TRIPLETS:\nTo identify instrument-verb-target triplets, use the graph as follows:\n\n1. IDENTIFY INSTRUMENTS vs ANATOMY:\n   - Examine each object's visual appearance\n   - Instruments: grasper, bipolar, hook, scissors, clipper, irrigator\n   - Anatomical targets: gallbladder, cystic_plate, cystic_duct, cystic_artery, etc.\n\n2. IDENTIFY INTERACTIONS (edges):\n   - Look for edges with SMALL distances (objects are close/touching)\n   - An edge between an instrument and anatomy suggests potential interaction\n   - Multiple edges to the same instrument suggest it's the active tool\n\n3. IDENTIFY ACTIONS (temporal changes):\n   - Compare spatial properties across timesteps t=0, t=1, t=2, ...\n   - CONSISTENT close distance + stable position = \"grasp\" or \"retract\"\n   - DECREASING distance over time = approaching for an action\n   - STABLE small distance + changing target properties = \"dissect\", \"coagulate\", \"cut\"\n   - Objects moving together = \"retract\"\n   - Instrument near multiple small scattered objects = \"irrigate\", \"aspirate\"\n\n4. CONFIRM with VISUAL APPEARANCE:\n   - Always verify the action by examining the object images\n   - Graph structure provides spatial-temporal context, but visual confirmation is required\n\nYou answer ONLY based on the scene graph and object images provided.\nYou keep responses concise while answering all aspects of the question.\n"}]}, {"role": "user", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<scene-graph>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<objects>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<object id=\"0\">"}, {"type": "image", "image": null}, {"type": "text", "text": "</object>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<object id=\"1\">"}, {"type": "image", "image": null}, {"type": "text", "text": "</object>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<object id=\"2\">"}, {"type": "image", "image": null}, {"type": "text", "text": "</object>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<object id=\"3\">"}, {"type": "image", "image": null}, {"type": "text", "text": "</object>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<object id=\"4\">"}, {"type": "image", "image": null}, {"type": "text", "text": "</object>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<object id=\"5\">"}, {"type": "image", "image": null}, {"type": "text", "text": "</object>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<object id=\"6\">"}, {"type": "image", "image": null}, {"type": "text", "text": "</object>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<object id=\"7\">"}, {"type": "image", "image": null}, {"type": "text", "text": "</object>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<object id=\"8\">"}, {"type": "image", "image": null}, {"type": "text", "text": "</object>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<object id=\"9\">"}, {"type": "image", "image": null}, {"type": "text", "text": "</object>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<object id=\"10\">"}, {"type": "image", "image": null}, {"type": "text", "text": "</object>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<object id=\"11\">"}, {"type": "image", "image": null}, {"type": "text", "text": "</object>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<object id=\"12\">"}, {"type": "image", "image": null}, {"type": "text", "text": "</object>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "