type": "text", "text": "<edge from=\"6\" to=\"6\" dist=\"1.00\"/>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<edge from=\"6\" to=\"10\" dist=\"0.15\"/>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<edge from=\"7\" to=\"4\" dist=\"0.05\"/>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<edge from=\"7\" to=\"7\" dist=\"1.00\"/>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<edge from=\"7\" to=\"9\" dist=\"0.09\"/>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<edge from=\"7\" to=\"10\" dist=\"0.08\"/>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<edge from=\"8\" to=\"2\" dist=\"0.12\"/>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<edge from=\"8\" to=\"8\" dist=\"1.00\"/>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<edge from=\"9\" to=\"7\" dist=\"0.09\"/>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<edge from=\"9\" to=\"9\" dist=\"1.00\"/>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<edge from=\"10\" to=\"4\" dist=\"0.08\"/>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<edge from=\"10\" to=\"6\" dist=\"0.15\"/>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<edge from=\"10\" to=\"7\" dist=\"0.08\"/>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<edge from=\"10\" to=\"10\" dist=\"1.00\"/>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "</spatial-graph>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "</spatial-graphs>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "</scene-graph>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<question>"}, {"type": "text", "text": "YOUR TASK: Identify instrument-verb-target triplets that are CURRENTLY ACTIVE based on the scene graph.\n\nCRITICAL RULES:\n1. Use the scene graph's spatial relationships (edges with small distances) to identify which instruments are interacting with which targets\n2. Use temporal evolution of node positions and edge distances to determine the action/verb\n3. Verify your graph-based inference by examining the object images\n4. ONLY report triplets where BOTH spatial proximity (edges) AND visual appearance confirm the interaction\n5. If an instrument has no close edges to anatomical structures, do NOT report it\n6. DO NOT use speculative language: \"appears\", \"seems\", \"likely\", \"possibly\", \"might be\"\n7. DO NOT infer based on typical procedures - only use the graph and images provided\n8. An empty response {\"triplets\": []} is CORRECT if no clear interactions are found\n\nVALID CATEGORIES:\n\"instrument\": {\"0\": \"grasper\", \"1\": \"bipolar\", \"2\": \"hook\", \"3\": \"scissors\", \"4\": \"clipper\", \"5\": \"irrigator\"}\n\"verb\": {\"0\": \"grasp\", \"1\": \"retract\", \"2\": \"dissect\", \"3\": \"coagulate\", \"4\": \"clip\", \"5\": \"cut\", \"6\": \"aspirate\", \"7\": \"irrigate\", \"8\": \"pack\", \"9\": \"null_verb\"}\n\"target\": {\"0\": \"gallbladder\", \"1\": \"cystic_plate\", \"2\": \"cystic_duct\", \"3\": \"cystic_artery\", \"4\": \"cystic_pedicle\", \"5\": \"blood_vessel\", \"6\": \"fluid\", \"7\": \"abdominal_wall_cavity\", \"8\": \"liver\", \"9\": \"adhesion\", \"10\": \"omentum\", \"11\": \"peritoneum\", \"12\": \"gut\", \"13\": \"specimen_bag\", \"14\": \"null_target\"}\n\nANALYSIS PROCEDURE:\n1. Identify all instruments and anatomical targets from the object images\n2. For each instrument, examine its edges across all timesteps to find close interactions (small distance values)\n3. Analyze how edge distances and node positions change over time to determine the action\n4. Verify the interaction visually by examining the object images\n5. Report only triplets with strong spatial-temporal evidence AND visual confirmation\n\nRESPONSE FORMAT:\nFirst, list the objects identified (instruments and anatomy).\nThen, describe spatial relationships (close edges) indicating interactions.\nThen, describe temporal changes indicating specific actions.\nFinally, output ONLY the triplets you are certain about based on graph structure + visual confirmation.\n\nIf uncertain or no clear interactions found, return: {\"triplets\": []}\n\nExample of GOOD response:\n\"Objects: grasper (id=0), gallbladder (id=3), bipolar (id=1), blood_vessel (id=5).\nSpatial relationships: Edges show grasper-gallbladder distance consistently <0.05 across all timesteps. Bipolar-vessel distance is <0.03 at t=1,2,3.\nTemporal changes: Grasper-gallbladder edge remains stable (grasping). Bipolar-vessel edge stable while vessel properties change (coagulating).\nVisual confirmation: Grasper visibly holds gallbladder. Bipolar in contact with vessel.\"\n{\"triplets\": [\n  {\"instrument\": \"grasper\", \"verb\": \"grasp\", \"target\": \"gallbladder\"},\n  {\"instrument\": \"bipolar\", \"verb\": \"coagulate\", \"target\": \"blood_vessel\"}\n]}\n\nExample of BAD response:\n\"A hook object is visible and is near the cystic duct in the graph, so it might be dissecting.\"\n{\"triplets\": [{\"instrument\": \"hook\", \"verb\": \"dissect\", \"target\": \"cystic_duct\"}]}\n(BAD because: does not cite specific edge distances, does not verify temporal changes, uses speculative language)\n\nOutput format:\n{\n  \"triplets\": [\n    {\"instrument\": \"...\", \"verb\": \"...\", \"target\": \"...\"}\n  ]\n}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "</question>\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\nYour response:\n"}]}]